    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "EVANSTON, Ill.\n\u2013 The No. 12 USC baseball team hit four home runs to take down Northwestern, 15-1, in seven innings on Friday afternoon in Evanston, moving to 18-0 on the season.\nUSC had 13 hits and also got another stellar performance on the mound from\nMason Edwards\nto move to 4-0 in Big Ten play. Northwestern falls to 6-8-1 overall and 0-1 in conference action.\nAbbrie Covarrubias\nand\nAdrian Lopez\neach hit two-run homers in the third inning as USC would score in each of the last five frames to pick up their third run-rule victory of the season. Lopez finished with three hits and four RBI, falling just a double short of a cycle.\nAndrew Lamb\nhomered in the fourth and\nRichard Tejeda\nhomered in the fifth. Tejeda's two-run shot in the fifth was part of a six-run innings for USC. Lamb has now homered in three straight games.\nEdwards tossed 6.0 innings, giving up three hits and just his first run of the season on a wind-aided home run to center. Edwards struck out 10 batters and walked just one. Through five starts on the year, he now owns a 0.30 ERA, with 52 strikeouts and 11 walks.\nFour Trojans had multiple hits and RBI in the game. Lopez's four RBI led the way, followed by Tejeda with three, and Covarrubias and\nKevin Takeuchi\nwith two.\nHenry Chabot\nset the side down in order in the seventh to end the game.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nAdrian Lopez\n: 3-for-4, 4 RBI, 3R, 2-R HR, 3B, BB\nAbbrie Covarrubias\n: 2-for-5, 2 RBI, 2R, 2-R HR\nRichard Tejeda\n: 1-for-3, 3 RBI, 2R, 2-R HR\nMason Edwards\n: 6.0 IP, 3H, R, BB, 10K\nCOMING UP\nUSC and Northwestern will wrap their series up with a doubleheader on Saturday. Both games will be broadcast on B1G+."
